{{About|the plant tissue|other uses|Epiblema (disambiguation)}}
{{Unreferenced|date=August 2010}}
In botany, '''Epiblem''' is a tissue that replaces the [[epidermis (botany)|epidermis]] in most roots and in stems of submerged aquatic plants. It is usually located between the epidermis and [[Cortex (botany)|cortex]] in the root or stem of a plant.

